Start
/ A read of config.json lands the file as {text, json}. Untouched, %cfg% is
/ the file's raw json *string* — not a parsed dict, not a JsonNode. This is
/ the Stage 4 + Decision (Part 1) row that flips structured-text MIMEs onto
/ {text, kind} so the value carries the json source until something asks.
/ Requires the config.json fixture committed alongside.
- read file 'config.json', write to %cfg%
- assert %cfg.Type.Name% equals "text"
- assert %cfg.Type.Kind% equals "json"
- assert %cfg% equals "{\"port\":8080}"
